case called briefly at 1:46pm and then again at 2:08pm. [MK]
Defendant Zachary R. Filenius in court with Attorney John V Rhiel.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.

On Motion of the State, the Court amends the charge to Misdemeanor Possession of THC contrary to Statute 961.41(3g)(e), and further, the Court strikes the "on or near a school" location enhancer. 

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; Elements recited; plea of " Guilty " entered; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Mr. Filenius guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Filenius on Probation for one year, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with all recommended treatment as required by the Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, therapy and counseling as required by the Agent
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take all prescribed medications as prescribed
--to submit to random urinalyses or other drug testing as required by the Agent 
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate by the Agent, and except for incidental contact as necessary for employment and educational programming; a further exception to this condition is that Mr. Filenius may have contact with Traci Glander
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--to pay costs of $243, plus $200 DNA surcharge, plus $25 drug testing fee, plus $66 in subpoena fees 

Days credit for time already served: 0  days

The Court indicates that if the DNA surcharge is found to be unconstitutional, and the Defendant has not yet paid the surcharge, then the Judgment of Conviction is to be amended to remove the surcharge payment requirement.  If the DNA surcharge has been paid and the ruling that found the DNA surcharge unconstitutional directs the clerks to reimburse the amount paid, then the clerk is to refund the amount paid to the Defendant. If the reimbursement is not mandated, then the amount will be kept.
recess 2:26pm.
